1	# HTML Presentation Template
2	
3	Reference architecture for generating slide presentations. Every presentation follows a fixed 16:9 stage model: slides are authored at 1920×1080 and the whole stage scales to fit the browser window.
4	
5	## Base HTML Structure
6	
7	```html
8	<!DOCTYPE html>
9	<html lang="en">
10	<head>
11	    <meta charset="UTF-8">
12	    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
13	    <title>Presentation Title</title>
14	
15	    <!-- Fonts: use Fontshare or Google Fonts — never system fonts -->
16	    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=...">
17	
18	    <style>
19	        /* ===========================================
20	           CSS CUSTOM PROPERTIES (THEME)
21	           Change these to change the whole look
22	           =========================================== */
23	        :root {
24	            /* Colors — from chosen style preset */
25	            --bg-primary: #0a0f1c;
26	            --bg-secondary: #111827;
27	            --text-primary: #ffffff;
28	            --text-secondary: #9ca3af;
29	            --accent: #00ffcc;
30	            --accent-glow: rgba(0, 255, 204, 0.3);
31	
32	            /* Typography — authored at 1920×1080 stage size */
33	            --font-display: 'Clash Display', sans-serif;
34	            --font-body: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
35	            --title-size: 112px;
36	            --subtitle-size: 34px;
37	            --body-size: 28px;
38	
39	            /* Spacing — authored at 1920×1080 stage size */
40	            --slide-padding: 72px;
41	            --content-gap: 32px;
42	
43	            /* Animation */
44	            --ease-out-expo: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
45	            --duration-normal: 0.6s;
46	        }
47	
48	        /* ===========================================
49	           BASE STYLES
50	           =========================================== */
51	        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
52	
53	        /* --- PASTE viewport-base.css CONTENTS HERE --- */
54	
55	        /* ===========================================
56	           ANIMATIONS
57	           Trigger via .visible class on the active slide
58	           =========================================== */
59	        .reveal {
60	            opacity: 0;
61	            transform: translateY(30px);
62	            transition: opacity var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-expo),
63	                        transform var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out-expo);
64	        }
65	
66	        .slide.visible .reveal {
67	            opacity: 1;
68	            transform: translateY(0);
69	        }
70	
71	        /* Stagger children for sequential reveal */
72	        .reveal:nth-child(1) { transition-delay: 0.1s; }
73	        .reveal:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.2s; }
74	        .reveal:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.3s; }
75	        .reveal:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 0.4s; }
76	
77	        /* ... preset-specific styles ... */
78	    </style>
79	</head>
80	<body>
81	    <div class="deck-viewport">
82	        <main class="deck-stage" id="deckStage">
83	            <section class="slide title-slide active">
84	                <h1 class="reveal">Presentation Title</h1>
85	                <p class="reveal">Subtitle or author</p>
86	            </section>
87	
88	            <section class="slide">
89	                <div class="slide-content">
90	                    <h2 class="reveal">Slide Title</h2>
91	                    <p class="reveal">Content...</p>
92	                </div>
93	            </section>
94	
95	            <!-- More slides... -->
96	        </main>
97	    </div>
98	
99	    <script>
100	        /* ===========================================
101	           SLIDE PRESENTATION CONTROLLER
102	           =========================================== */
103	        class SlidePresentation {
104	            constructor() {
105	                this.slides = document.querySelectorAll('.slide');
106	                this.currentSlide = 0;
107	                this.stage = document.getElementById('deckStage');
108	                this.setupStageScale();
109	                this.setupKeyboardNav();
110	                this.setupTouchNav();
111	                this.showSlide(0);
112	            }
113	
114	            setupStageScale() {
115	                const scale = () => {
116	                    const factor = Math.min(window.innerWidth / 1920, window.innerHeight / 1080);
117	                    const x = (window.innerWidth - 1920 * factor) / 2;
118	                    const y = (window.innerHeight - 1080 * factor) / 2;
119	                    this.stage.style.transform = `translate(${x}px, ${y}px) scale(${factor})`;
120	                };
121	                scale();
122	                window.addEventListener('resize', scale);
123	            }
124	
125	            setupKeyboardNav() {
126	                // Arrow keys, Space, Page Up/Down
127	            }
128	
129	            setupTouchNav() {
130	                // Touch/swipe support for mobile
131	            }
132	
133	            showSlide(index) {
134	                this.currentSlide = Math.max(0, Math.min(index, this.slides.length - 1));
135	                this.slides.forEach((slide, i) => {
136	                    slide.classList.toggle('active', i === this.currentSlide);
137	                    slide.classList.toggle('visible', i === this.currentSlide);
138	                });
139	            }
140	        }
141	
142	        new SlidePresentation();
143	    </script>
144	</body>
145	</html>
146	```
147	
148	## Required JavaScript Features
149	
150	Every presentation must include:
151	
152	1. **SlidePresentation Class** — Main controller with:
153	   - Keyboard navigation (arrows, space, page up/down)
154	   - Touch/swipe support
155	   - Mouse wheel navigation
156	   - Optional progress indicator or page count, kept outside the slide stage
157	
158	2. **Stage Scaling** — For fixed 16:9 presentation behavior:
159	   - Keep all slides at 1920×1080 inside `.deck-stage`
160	   - Scale the whole stage with one transform
161	   - Letterbox/pillarbox as needed; never reflow slide content per device
162	
163	3. **Optional Enhancements** (match to chosen style):
164	   - Custom cursor with trail
165	   - Particle system background (canvas)
166	   - Parallax effects
167	   - 3D tilt on hover
168	   - Magnetic buttons
169	   - Counter animations
170	
171	4. **Inline Editing** (included by default after draft generation):
172	   - Edit toggle button (hidden by default, revealed via hover hotzone or `E` key)
173	   - Auto-save to localStorage
174	   - Export/save file functionality
175	   - See "Inline Editing Implementation" section below
176	
177	## Inline Editing Implementation
178	
179	Inline editing is a lightweight post-draft affordance. Do not ask the user whether they want it during the pre-generation Q&A. Include it by default unless the user explicitly asks for a locked/export-only presentation or no editing controls.
180	
181	**Do NOT use CSS `~` sibling selector for hover-based show/hide.** The CSS-only approach (`edit-hotzone:hover ~ .edit-toggle`) fails because `pointer-events: none` on the toggle button breaks the hover chain: user hovers hotzone -> button becomes visible -> mouse moves toward button -> leaves hotzone -> button disappears before click.
182	
183	**Required approach: JS-based hover with 400ms delay timeout.**
184	
185	HTML:
186	```html
187	<div class="edit-hotzone"></div>
188	<button class="edit-toggle" id="editToggle" title="Edit mode (E)">✏️</button>
189	```
190	
191	CSS (visibility controlled by JS classes only):
192	```css
193	/* Do NOT use CSS ~ sibling selector for this!
194	   pointer-events: none breaks the hover chain.
195	   Must use JS with delay timeout. */
196	.edit-hotzone {
197	    position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0;
198	    width: 80px; height: 80px;
199	    z-index: 10000;
200	    cursor: pointer;
201	}
202	.edit-toggle {
203	    opacity: 0;
204	    pointer-events: none;
205	    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
206	    z-index: 10001;
207	}
208	.edit-toggle.show,
209	.edit-toggle.active {
210	    opacity: 1;
211	    pointer-events: auto;
212	}
213	```
214	
215	JS (three interaction methods):
216	```javascript
217	// 1. Click handler on the toggle button
218	document.getElementById('editToggle').addEventListener('click', () => {
219	    editor.toggleEditMode();
220	});
221	
222	// 2. Hotzone hover with 400ms grace period
223	const hotzone = document.querySelector('.edit-hotzone');
224	const editToggle = document.getElementById('editToggle');
225	let hideTimeout = null;
226	
227	hotzone.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
228	    clearTimeout(hideTimeout);
229	    editToggle.classList.add('show');
230	});
231	hotzone.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
232	    hideTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
233	        if (!editor.isActive) editToggle.classList.remove('show');
234	    }, 400);
235	});
236	editToggle.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
237	    clearTimeout(hideTimeout);
238	});
239	editToggle.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
240	    hideTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
241	        if (!editor.isActive) editToggle.classList.remove('show');
242	    }, 400);
243	});
244	
245	// 3. Hotzone direct click
246	hotzone.addEventListener('click', () => {
247	    editor.toggleEditMode();
248	});
249	
250	// 4. Keyboard shortcut (E key, skip when editing text)
251	document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
252	    if ((e.key === 'e' || e.key === 'E') && !e.target.getAttribute('contenteditable')) {
253	        editor.toggleEditMode();
254	    }
255	});
256	```
257	
258	## Image Pipeline (Skip If No Images)
259	
260	If user chose "No images" in Phase 1, skip this entirely. If images were provided, process them before generating HTML.
261	
262	**Dependency:** `pip install Pillow`
263	
264	### Image Processing
265	
266	```python
267	from PIL import Image, ImageDraw
268	
269	# Circular crop (for logos on modern/clean styles)
270	def crop_circle(input_path, output_path):
271	    img = Image.open(input_path).convert('RGBA')
272	    w, h = img.size
273	    size = min(w, h)
274	    left, top = (w - size) // 2, (h - size) // 2
275	    img = img.crop((left, top, left + size, top + size))
276	    mask = Image.new('L', (size, size), 0)
277	    ImageDraw.Draw(mask).ellipse([0, 0, size, size], fill=255)
278	    img.putalpha(mask)
279	    img.save(output_path, 'PNG')
280	
281	# Resize (for oversized images that inflate HTML)
282	def resize_max(input_path, output_path, max_dim=1200):
283	    img = Image.open(input_path)
284	    img.thumbnail((max_dim, max_dim), Image.LANCZOS)
285	    img.save(output_path, quality=85)
286	```
287	
288	| Situation | Operation |
289	|-----------|-----------|
290	| Square logo on rounded aesthetic | `crop_circle()` |
291	| Image > 1MB | `resize_max(max_dim=1200)` |
292	| Wrong aspect ratio | Manual crop with `img.crop()` |
293	
294	Save processed images with `_processed` suffix. Never overwrite originals.
295	
296	### Image Placement
297	
298	**Use direct file paths** (not base64) — presentations are viewed locally:
299	
300	```html
301	<img src="assets/logo_round.png" alt="Logo" class="slide-image logo">
302	<img src="assets/screenshot.png" alt="Screenshot" class="slide-image screenshot">
303	```
304	
305	```css
306	.slide-image {
307	    max-width: 100%;
308	    max-height: min(50vh, 400px);
309	    object-fit: contain;
310	    border-radius: 8px;
311	}
312	.slide-image.screenshot {
313	    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
314	    border-radius: 12px;
315	    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
316	}
317	.slide-image.logo {
318	    max-height: min(30vh, 200px);
319	}
320	```
321	
322	**Adapt border/shadow colors to match the chosen style's accent.** Never repeat the same image on multiple slides (except logos on title + closing).
323	
324	**Placement patterns:** Logo centered on title slide. Screenshots in two-column layouts with text. Full-bleed images as slide backgrounds with text overlay (use sparingly).
325	
326	---
327	
328	## Code Quality
329	
330	**Comments:** Every section needs clear comments explaining what it does and how to modify it.
331	
332	**Accessibility:**
333	- Semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`)
334	- Keyboard navigation works fully
335	- ARIA labels where needed
336	- `prefers-reduced-motion` support (included in viewport-base.css)
337	
338	## File Structure
339	
340	Single presentations:
341	```
342	presentation.html    # Self-contained, all CSS/JS inline
343	assets/              # Images only, if any
344	```
345	
346	Multiple presentations in one project:
347	```
348	[name].html
349	[name]-assets/
350	```
